OL,3,CYeovil police officer tried to have
OL,4,Crelationship with domestic abuse victim
OL,6,F"He failed to act with self-control,
OL,7,Ffailed to treat her with respect or
OL,8,Fcourtesy and abused his position as a
OL,9,Fpolice officer.
OL,11,F"He behaved in a manner that
OL,12,Fundermines public confidence in the
OL,13,Fpolice service."
OL,15,FMr Ley-Morgan said PC Z, who did not
OL,16,Fattend the hearing at force
OL,17,Fheadquarters in Portishead on
OL,18,FWednesday 19 February, made a full
OL,19,Fadmission of the facts, the alleged
OL,20,Fbreaches of standards of professional
OL,21,Fbehaviour and gross misconduct.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUuD@PO]
